In this proclamation issued by President Donald Trump, he reaffirms the commitment to providing all Americans with affordable and high-quality education. He acknowledges the importance of parents, guardians, teachers, and school leaders in preparing children for the workforce. The proclamation emphasizes the need for education to be tailored to each student's unique needs and encourages parents, educators, and school leaders to rethink the way students learn. Trump also highlights the significance of high-quality education in building a strong workforce and mentions the establishment of the President's National Council for the American Worker and the American Workforce Policy Advisory Board. He concludes by proclaiming November 11 through November 17, 2018, as American Education Week and calls on states and communities to support high-quality education for all students.